libmodbus
------------------------------------------
libmodbus is a C library designed to provide a fast and robust implementation
of the Modbus protocol. It runs on Linux, Mac OS X, FreeBSD, QNX and Windows.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.4-1
  libmodbus-devel-3.1.11-1bl1
  libmodbus5-3.1.11-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libtool-2.5.3-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://libmodbus.org/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/stephane/libmodbus/releases/download/v3.1.11/libmodbus-3.1.11.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libmodbus-3.1.11-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libmodbus-3.1.11-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libmodbus-3.1.11-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmodbus-3.1.11-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmodbus5-3.1.11-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmodbus-devel-3.1.11-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libmodbus)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libmodbus.README
  /usr/share/doc/libmodbus/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libmodbus/COPYING.LESSER
  /usr/share/doc/libmodbus/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/libmodbus/README.md

(libmodbus5)
  /usr/bin/cygmodbus-5.dll

(libmodbus-devel)
  /usr/include/modbus/modbus-rtu.h
  /usr/include/modbus/modbus-tcp.h
  /usr/include/modbus/modbus-version.h
  /usr/include/modbus/modbus.h
  /usr/lib/libmodbus.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libmodbus.pc

